# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  JobDash environment — copy to `.env` and fill in.
#  Use `.env` (not `.env.local`): Next.js reads both, but the Prisma CLI
#  (`prisma db push`, `prisma studio`) only reads `.env`.
#  `.env` is gitignored. On Vercel, add these under
#  Project → Settings → Environment Variables.
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── NVIDIA Nemotron (required for AI generation) ─────────────────────────
#  Get a free key: https://build.nvidia.com  →  open any Nemotron model
#  →  "Get API Key".  The endpoint is OpenAI-compatible.
NVIDIA_API_KEY=nvapi-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
NVIDIA_BASE_URL=https://integrate.api.nvidia.com/v1
NVIDIA_MODEL=nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b

# ── Database (required for saving your resume + history) ─────────────────
#  A serverless Postgres works best on Vercel. Free options:
#    • Neon:            https://neon.tech        (recommended)
#    • Vercel Postgres: Storage tab in your Vercel project
#  Use the *pooled* connection string.
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@host/dbname?sslmode=require

# ── Notion sync (OPTIONAL — the app works fully without it) ──────────────
#  1. Create an internal integration: https://www.notion.so/my-integrations
#  2. Copy its "Internal Integration Secret" into NOTION_TOKEN.
#  3. Create a database with columns: Company (title), Role (text),
#     Status (select), URL (url), Date Applied (date).
#  4. Share that database with your integration (••• → Connections).
#  5. Copy the database ID from its URL into NOTION_DATABASE_ID.
NOTION_TOKEN=
NOTION_DATABASE_ID=
